Definition.WordDefinition: walk in v : enter by walking; "She walks in at all hours, as if she lived here"

walk-in adj : (of e.g. closets or refrigerators) extending very far enough back to allow a person to enter; "a deep walk-in refrigerator"; "walk-in closets" [syn: {walk-in(a)}] n 1: person who walks in without having an appointment; "the emergency room was overrun with walk-ins" 2: an operative who initiates his own defection (usually to a hostile country) for political asylum 3: an assured victory (especially in an election) [syn: {waltz}] 4: a small room large enough to admit entrance
